Heart disease is one of the leading causes of death worldwide. Early prediction and diagnosis are crucial in reducing the risk and managing the condition effectively. This project leverages machine learning algorithms to predict the likelihood of heart disease based on various health indicators.

üõ†Ô∏è Features
Data Preprocessing: Handling missing values, scaling, and encoding categorical variables.
Feature Engineering: Creating new features from existing data to improve model accuracy.
Modeling: Implementing various machine learning algorithms such as Logistic Regression, Random Forest, and Support Vector Machine (SVM).
Evaluation: Assessing model performance using metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.
Visualization: Plotting important features, confusion matrix, and ROC curves to understand model behavior.
